  "title": "Question : Need tutorials for creating widgets",
  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nFirstly, I'm not an jquery expert.\r\n\r\nI don't figure out how to custom a widget (RefinementList) to implement a multiple attributes name query.\r\nFor example, i need to query on best_offer.merchant.name or other_offers.merchant.name...\r\n\r\nThe [doc](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectRefinementList.html#struct-CustomRefinementListWidgetOptions) only related to design the render... Or i miss something ?\r\n\r\nThe page related to custom widget is completly unclear (i read also all links on this page) : \r\nhttps://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/custom-widget.html\r\n\r\nI don't understand what i have to do firstly.\r\n\r\nThanks for your Help\r\n\r\n",
